                <h2 class="section-title">Understanding Your Results</h2>
                <div class="results-table">
                  <div class="result-row">
                    <span class="result-level">Low Iron & Low Ferritin</span>
                    <span class="result-meaning">Suggestive of iron deficiency anemia</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="result-row">
                    <span class="result-level">High Iron & High Ferritin</span>
                    <span class="result-meaning">May indicate iron overload (hemochromatosis) or inflammation</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="result-row">
                    <span class="result-level">Low Ferritin, Normal Iron</span>
                    <span class="result-meaning">Possible early iron deficiency</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="result-row">
                    <span class="result-level">High TIBC</span>
                    <span class="result-meaning">Common in iron deficiency</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="result-row">
                    <span class="result-level">Low TIBC</span>
                    <span class="result-meaning">May occur in chronic illness or iron overload</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mt-4">
                  Note: Reference ranges vary; results should be interpreted by a healthcare provider in context of overall health.
                </p>
              </div>

              <!-- FAQ -->
              <div class="content-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <div class="faq-container">
                  <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">Is fasting required for the Iron Panel?</summary>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Fasting for 8–12 hours is recommended for the most accurate results, particularly for serum iron levels.</p>
                  </details>
                  
                  <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">What's the difference between iron and ferritin?</summary>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Serum iron measures circulating iron in your blood, while ferritin indicates stored iron in your body tissues.</p>
                  </details>
                  
                  <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">How long until I get my results?</summary>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Typically within 1–3 business days after your blood draw.</p>
                  </details>
                  
                  <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary class="faq-question">Can I take iron supplements before the test?</summary>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Discuss with your healthcare provider, as iron supplements may affect test results and should be discontinued before testing if recommended.</p>
                  </details>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Compliance & Trust -->
              <div class="cta-section">
                <p class="cta-text">
                  <strong>CLIA-Certified & HIPAA-Compliant.</strong> This test is processed by Quest Diagnostics, 
                  a trusted lab network. Your information is protected and results are reviewed by qualified medical professionals.
                </p>
              </div>

              <!-- Related Tests -->
              <div class="content-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">Related Tests</h2>
                <div class="related-tests">
                  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Often ordered with:</p>
                  <div class="related-links">
                    <a href="/tests/general-health/blood-counts/cbc" class="link-item">Complete Blood Count (CBC) →</a>
                    <a href="/tests/general-health/vitamins/vitamin-b12" class="link-item">Vitamin B12 Test →</a>
                    <a href="/tests/general-health/vitamins/vitamin-d" class="link-item">Vitamin D Test →</a>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</ShoppingLayout>

<style>
  .marketing-section {
    margin-top: 4rem;
